# MEMORY.md — The Index

> This is LeRoy's memory index — one line per note, loaded into context every session so
> LeRoy knows what it knows. It is **maintained automatically**: every time a note is written
> to the vault, a one-line pointer is added here. You rarely edit this by hand.

Each line looks like:

```
- [Short Title](Projects/some-note.md) — one-line hook of what's inside
```

The hook is what LeRoy scans to decide whether a note is relevant to your current request,
then it opens the full file only if it is. Keep hooks short and specific.

